The Management of the University of Benin (UNIBEN) has suspended services in its Health Centre to enable it fumigate the centre to further curtail the spread of coronavirus.  Dr Benedicta Ehanire, the Public Relations Officer of the institution, announced the suspension in a statement on Friday in Benin. “As part of proactive measures to check the ravaging COVID-19, services will be suspended temporarily for five days starting from Saturday, June 27 to Wednesday, July 1.” “This is for fumigation to be carried out in line with Federal Government’s guidelines.” “During this period and after, the medical helplines will remain operational.” “The helplines are: 08163104400, 0802291100, 08023367827 and 08033885998,’’ she stated.